## Session log

_Newest first. Add one entry per working session or merge-worthy update._

### 2026-05-21 — Countdowns

- **Summary:** Completed batch action flow from UI prototype to API-backed behavior. Preserved simplified multi-select UX (header icon toggle + highlighted active state), kept floating action bar always present in multi-select for "Use all visible", switched intrusive top-drop messaging to toast notifications, and added Archive as a batch action.
- **Backend/API:** Added batch endpoints for cadence reschedule, retag, archive/unarchive, and delete in `server/crudApi.js` with partial-success handling and skipped/no-cadence reporting.
- **Frontend wiring:** Connected batch UI actions to live API callers in `public/actions.js` and `public/app.js`.
- **UX behavior:** Removed top selected-count emphasis; floating action bar serves as active selection/scope indicator. Bar floats above content and does not push scroll layout.
- **Result messaging:** Uses toast-based success/warning feedback, including explicit "not rescheduled (no cadence)" item listing on cadence reschedule.
- **Testing:** Added/updated API tests for batch operations in `tests/api-events.test.js`; full suite passing (`95/95`).
- **Notes:** Batch actions are no longer UI-only; they now execute real local API behavior.

